    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Doesn't wrapping have to be enforced some way or another? Otherwise output will overflow page boundaries.\n\nThis doesn't apply to raw cells - remember, raw cells are raw latex input, the _entire point of which_ is that we don't touch them, no matter what.\n\nFor colored output, we are clearly doing the wrapping wrong, because we are measuring color escapes as part of the column width, so we are effectively wrapping at about 20 characters.\n\nI didn't say we shouldn't wrap, just that we should _never_ wrap raw cells (obvious) and we should be more careful about what we measure for text output, since we are currently measuring incorrectly.\n"
